  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" UCO Bank & Anr. versus Vijay Kumar Handa pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_5_389_400','2025INSC442'); ><font size='4'> <strong>UCO BANK & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>VIJAY KUMAR HANDA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 389</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 442</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001662025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The appellant-Bank dismissed the respondent from the services. Whether the respondent was entitled to receive the terminal benefits for the period of service he had rendered. Headnotes&dagger; Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 &ndash; Industrial Disputes (Central) Rules, 1957 Clause 19.5(c) &ndash; UCO Bank (Employees&rsquo;) Pension Regulations, 1995 &ndash; Respondent was serving as a Clerk in the appellant Bank &ndash; Respondent was dismissed from the services on the charges of indulging in riotous, disorderly and indecent behaviour within the premises of the Bank<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 02-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5922/2024</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_5_389_400','2025INSC442','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn b